#: ../../../advanced/wheel_sdks.md:1
msgid "VTK Wheel SDKs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/wheel_sdks.md:3
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/wheel_sdks.md:5
msgid ""
"VTK Wheel SDKs are Python wheels that contains a snapshot of VTK CI install "
"directory. They are available at https://vtk.org/files/wheel-sdks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/wheel_sdks.md:8
msgid ""
"VTK install directory contains everything that is needed to build VTK native "
"extensions and wrap them in Python. When built against the SDK, these native "
"extensions can use the VTK wheel native libraries (DLLs, SOs or DyLibs)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/wheel_sdks.md:11
msgid "This enables the following features:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/wheel_sdks.md:12
msgid ""
"Enable subclassing `vtkObject` based classes and have them work natively "
"with VTK own objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/wheel_sdks.md:13
msgid ""
"Enable sharing `vtkObject` between different Python wheels without issues."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/wheel_sdks.md:14
msgid ""
"Enable exposing VTK in public APIs of Python wheels that contains native (C+"
"+) VTK code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/wheel_sdks.md:15
msgid "Remove the need to package VTK in every wheel that uses it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/wheel_sdks.md:17
msgid ""
"Each wheel distributed on [VTK GitLab Package Registry](https://gitlab."
"kitware.com/vtk/vtk/-/packages), have its corresponding wheel SDK, starting "
"with VTK 9.6.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/wheel_sdks.md:19
msgid "How to use the VTK Wheel SDKs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/wheel_sdks.md:21
msgid ""
"VTK Wheel SDKs are intended to be consumed \"build-system requirements\" "
"with [scikit-build-core](https://scikit-build-core.readthedocs.io/en/"
"latest/) Python build backend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/wheel_sdks.md:23
msgid ""
"The VTK Wheel SDKs include a [scikit-build-core entry-point](https://scikit-"
"build-core.readthedocs.io/en/latest/configuration/search_paths.html). This "
"enables projects to automatically find the VTK installation from the wheel "
"SDKs, using a regular `find_package(VTK)`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/wheel_sdks.md:26
msgid ""
"For more information about how to use the wheels SDK, please refer to the "
"\"Build/VTKPythonExtensions\" example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/wheel_sdks.md:28
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/wheel_sdks.md:30
msgid ""
"The VTK wheel SDK is also distributed as `tar.xz` archives, this is "
"deprecated in favor of the `.whl`, and may be removed in future versions. "
"Note that a `.whl` is a ZIP archive, and its content may be used as-is. The "
"same content as in the `tar.xz` archives can be found in the `vtk_sdk/"
"content` folder of the `.whl`."
msgstr ""
